    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. that's a good start. specifically, some of the more conservative legal scholars argue that this idea of \"substantive\" due process is actually just a way for judges to make up new rights that aren't written in the Constitution. can you explain why that perspective might be considered a valid critique of the doctrine?",
